# Typed errors

Always define named error classes. Never `raise "message"` with a bare string.

Error names must be specific to the class — prefix with the class name when the
error type is otherwise generic (e.g. `BrewInfoError` not `InfoError`).

```ruby
# BAD
raise "brew info failed"
raise "Could not resolve ref"

# GOOD
class BrewInfoError < StandardError; end
raise BrewInfoError, "brew info --json=v1 #{formula} failed"
```

Every typed error must have a corresponding test that asserts the specific class:

```ruby
# In RSpock tests
When "fetching a bad formula"
repository.fetch(bad_id)

Then
raises Dev::Deps::BrewRepository::BrewInfoError
```
